== Character Expressions ==

Characters display emotions based on gameplay:

=== Positive Events ===
* Clearing lines: Happy/excited
* Chain combos: Very happy
* Winning: Celebration animation

=== Negative Events ===
* Screen filling up: Worried/nervous
* Receiving garbage: Surprised
* Losing: Sad/defeated

== Story Context ==

While Yoshi's Cookie has minimal story, the premise involves:
* Yoshi organizing cookies in his kitchen
* Mario and friends participating in cookie competitions
* Bowser attempting to spoil the cookie party

== Trivia ==
* Yoshi's Cookie was originally an unrelated Japanese puzzle game called "Hermetica"
* The Nintendo characters were added for the Western release
* The game was developed by Bullet-Proof Software (later Blue Planet Software)
* The SNES version features enhanced graphics and additional modes

